text.section:
In carrying out its enforcement responsibilities, the department may:
Inspect and examine all premises in which or on which charitable gaming is conducted or charitable gaming supplies or equipment are manufactured or distributed;
Seize and remove from premises and impound charitable gaming supplies and equipment for the purposes of examination and inspection pursuant to an appropriate court order;
Demand access to, inspect, and audit books and records of licensees for the purpose of determining compliance with laws and administrative regulations relative to charitable gaming; and
Conduct in-depth audits and investigations, when warranted.

section.section:
A letter of warning issued under this section shall:
Identify the violation;
Describe the corrective action necessary;
Identify the administrative actions that can be taken if the violation is not addressed; and
Provide that the person shall have thirty (30) days to correct the action leading to the violation.
